# React & CSS Conventions

## Component structure
- Persona journey content lives in `src/data/controllerHealthJourneys.js` — add copy there, not inline in components
- Controller option pricing logic belongs in `ControllerHealthStepCard.jsx` (`getPricingDetails`)
- Avoid creating new top-level components; prefer extending existing ones unless the scope clearly warrants a new file

## State rules
- Proactive toast lifecycle state (`navigationCount`, `hasTriggered`, `isVisible`, `dismissed`) is local to `Ps5HomeScreen.jsx`
- Overlay step state (`stepIndex`, `selectedOptionId`) is local to `ControllerHealthOverlay.jsx`
- Do not lift these to `App.jsx` without discussing first

## Keyboard handling
- Always prevent keyboard events from propagating outside the overlay when it is open
- Never use `event.repeat` to count navigation moves; use the `useRef` pressedArrowKeys set

## CSS
- All styles live in `src/styles/ps5-console.css` — no inline `style` objects for anything beyond dynamic positioning
- Glassmorphism base: `background: rgba(15,15,18,0.82)` + `backdrop-filter: blur(24px) saturate(1.6)`
- Use `clamp()` for all font sizes and responsive dimensions
- Animations must have a `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` override
- `z-index` ladder: toast 1400, overlay-shell 1500, overlay 1600

## Images
- Always set `object-fit: contain` on controller images
- The thumbstick glow `.stick-glow` is positioned at `left: 66.9%; top: 56.8%` relative to `.issue-controller-wrap` — do not change without testing on a rendered page
